HEADWORD: Nitroform
<hw>Ni"tro*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Nitro-</ets>
+ <ets>form</ets>yl.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A nitro derivative
of methane, analogous to chloroform, obtained as a colorless oily or
crystalline substance, <chform>CH.(NO2)3</chform>, quite explosive, and
having well-defined acid properties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

